# Shared Component Rules

## Core Rules
- **No copy-paste JSX** — if a pattern appears more than once, extract it into a component
- **No inline components inside page files** — always create a separate file
- **Check HeroUI first** — see `heroui-usage.mdc`. Only write custom components when HeroUI doesn't have it
- **Marketing chrome** — landing CTAs, logo row, and catalog-style tags/media shells: use `CommonButton`, `BrandLogo`, `TagPill`, `MediaCard`, `SectionHeader` from `@/components/common` (see `ui-design-system.mdc`)
- **Use Tailwind classes** from `@theme` tokens — avoid `style={{ }}` except for gradients and glow shadows

## Directory Structure

```
src/components/
  pages/       ← UI tied to a route or feature area (see below)
  ui/          ← primitives NOT available in HeroUI (GlassCard, GradientText, SectionHeading)
  layout/      ← app chrome (headers, footers), not marketing page sections
  image/       ← image-processing specific components (shared across flows)
```

> **Button, Input, Modal, Tabs, Spinner, Progress, Chip/Badge** → use `@heroui/react/*`, do NOT recreate

---

## Page-scoped components — `src/components/pages/`

Use this tree for **feature- or route-specific** UI that should not pollute shared folders.

```
src/components/pages/
  boost/enhance-image/   ← dashboard enhancer (modals, upload zone, queue rows, …)
  marketing/             ← landing / marketing sections (hero, testimonials, …)
  pricing-plans/         ← `/pricing` page composition
```

**Rules**
- **App Router files stay thin** — `src/app/[locale]/.../page.tsx` imports from `@/components/pages/...` (and shared `ui/`, `layout/`). Avoid large JSX blobs in `page.tsx`.
- **Name folders by product area**, mirroring routes when it helps (`boost/...` for authenticated app, `marketing/` for public site blocks).
- **Still shared?** If two unrelated routes need the same component, move it to `ui/`, `layout/`, or `image/` instead of duplicating under `pages/`.
- **Colocate helpers** — hooks, constants, and small pure modules for that page can live next to the components (e.g. `useEnhancerUploadZone.ts`, `countEnhancerProcessingRows.ts`).

