## Image Components — `src/components/image/`

Create each file when implementing the corresponding feature.

### `OperationSelector.tsx` — grid for choosing image operation
- Props: `value: ImageOperation | null`, `onChange: (op: ImageOperation) => void`
- Grid of HeroUI `<Card>` items — each shows: icon, name, short description, `CreditCostBadge`
- Selected card: `border-brand/45` border + `bg-brand/10` background + `shadow-brand` glow
- Wrap in `<motion.div>` stagger on mount

### `ImageUploadZone.tsx` — drag & drop upload area
- Props: `onFile: (file: File) => void`, `disabled?: boolean`
- Dashed border: `border-2 border-dashed border-brand/45`
- `accept="image/jpeg,image/png,image/webp"` — validate MIME type on both client and server
- Show: icon, instruction text, "JPEG, PNG, WebP — max 20MB"

### `BeforeAfterSlider.tsx` — before/after image comparison (`'use client'`)
- Props: `beforeSrc`, `afterSrc`, `alt`
- `range input` overlay + CSS `clipPath: inset(0 ${100-pos}% 0 0)` to reveal
- Divider line: `bg-brand-light` class
- Animate slider handle with Framer Motion

### `JobStatusBadge.tsx` — HeroUI Chip mapped to job status
- `pending → default`, `processing → primary`, `completed → success`, `failed → danger`
- When `processing`: wrap in `<motion.div animate={{ opacity: [1, 0.5, 1] }} transition={{ repeat: Infinity }}>` for pulse

### `CreditCostBadge.tsx` — display credit cost
- HeroUI `<Chip color="secondary" variant="bordered">`
- Content: `✦ {n} credit{n > 1 ? 's' : ''}`

### `ProcessingProgress.tsx` — spinner while job is running
- HeroUI `<Spinner color="primary" size="lg">` inside `<GlassCard>`
- Primary text: `text-foreground` — "Added to queue…" / "Processing image…"
- Subtext: `text-subtle` — "Usually takes 10–30 seconds. Page will update automatically."

